</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E9AFDE1E3C85CD79A00306002B469ECD" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="1C81836023C4B8FD0B5CA9E5C18BE023" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F1ED942CB534FFBF18D18CE08D4C6720" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
New records: Southern Black Sea coast: Chernomorets, 27.07.2006, 3 m., 7 w.; same place, 31.07.2006, 1 w., leg. and det. L. Borowiec (DBET); Sinemorets, Butamyata loc., 16.04.2009, 1 q., 4 w., leg. ALG. Detailed occurrence data: 
<bibRefCitation id="50EBDAE48D6FD1E64E575157795D87A8" author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Data Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" refId="B7741022" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., Borowiec, L., 2022. New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria. In: Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." title="New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria" volumeTitle="Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." year="2022">Lapeva-Gjonova and Borowiec (2022)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B2AF93B38C46EBAAA894B031718533BC" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="notes">
<paragraph id="3263AB53EA190996A645FF237D33974C" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B83353CCB911D33E6FD0C592EF7AD521" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
<taxonomicName id="8E66E77DB20BC104A0B8F778AF7BEAE0" authorityName="Karaman" authorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Crematogaster" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Crematogaster gordani" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gordani">
<emphasis id="59A29A883DC2022D9A8D10AB067404AA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Crematogaster gordani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from Montenegro by 
<bibRefCitation id="CC32E1928B31CCCDE529831EE5DE24AF" author="Karaman, M." journalOrPublisher="Natura Montenegrina, Podgorica" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="5 - 24" refId="B7725786" refString="Karaman, M., 2008. Two new species of the Crematogaster scutellaris group, Crematogaster gordani, sp. nov. and C. montenigrinus sp. nov. (Insecta: Hymenoptera: Formicidae) from Crna Gora (Montenegro) with key of this group from Southern Europe. Natura Montenegrina, Podgorica 7 (1): 5 - 24" title="Two new species of the Crematogaster scutellaris group, Crematogaster gordani, sp. nov. and C. montenigrinus sp. nov. (Insecta: Hymenoptera: Formicidae) from Crna Gora (Montenegro) with key of this group from Southern Europe" volume="7" year="2008">Karaman (2008)</bibRefCitation>
. Presented record from Chernomorets is the sample based on which the species was reported from Bulgaria (
<bibRefCitation id="1C3A7406E2AE5F7A6D341E83C42BE18E" author="Borowiec, L." journalOrPublisher="Genus" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="1 - 340" refId="B7725633" refString="Borowiec, L., 2014. Catalogue of ants of Europe, the Mediterranean Basin and adjacent regions (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). Genus 25 (1-2): 1 - 340" title="Catalogue of ants of Europe, the Mediterranean Basin and adjacent regions (Hymenoptera: Formicidae)" volume="25" year="2014">Borowiec 2014</bibRefCitation>
). The second locality also is situated on the southern Black Sea coast.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
